{"model": "PD42-2-1240-CANopen", "excerpt": "PD42-1240 is a full mechatronic solution, made up of a TMCM-1240 stepper control module and a NEMA 17 (42mm flange size) motor. The PD42-1240 allows to control the module using TMCL\u2122 or CANopen firmware, making use of the Trinamic TMC5160 motion controller and motor driver. Dynamic current control, and quiet, smooth and efficient operation are combined with StealthChop\u2122, DcStep\u2122, StallGuard\u2122 and CoolStep\u2122 features.All you need to get started is a power supply and Trinamic's free and easy to use TMCL-IDE. This graphical user interface allows quick setup and supports the use of commands in direct mode, monitors real-time behavior visualized in graphs, and logs and stores data.More about the TMCL-IDESpecial FeaturesDcStep\u2122CoolStep\u2122SpreadCycle\u2122StallGuard2\u2122StealthChop\u2122", "fields": {"Status": "active", "Flange NEMA": "17", "Flange": "42mm", "Holding Torque": "36Ncm", "Motor Supply": "10\u202630V", "Microsteps": "1\u2026256", "CAN": "Yes", "RS485": "Yes", "Step/Dir": "Yes", "USB": "Yes", "SensOstep\u2122": "Yes", "TMCL\u2122": "", "CANopen": "Yes", "DcStep\u2122": "Yes", "SixPoint\u2122": "Yes", "CoolStep\u2122": "Yes", "SpreadCycle\u2122": "Yes", "StallGuard2\u2122": "Yes", "StealthChop\u2122": "Yes", "Width": "42mm", "Height": "42mm", "Length": "51mm"}, "picture": "https://trinamic.com/fileadmin/assets/Products/Drives_Images/PD42-2-1240.jpg", "images": ["https://trinamic.com/fileadmin/assets/Products/Modules_Blockdiagrams/PD-1240_Blockdiagramm.svg"], "resource": {"Datasheet": [["Hardware Manual Rev 1.03", "https://trinamic.com/fileadmin/assets/Products/Drives_Documents/PD-1240_hardware_manual_hw1.10_rev1.03.pdf"]], "Documentation": [["CANopen Firmware Manual FW V3.22 Rev V1.01", "https://trinamic.com/fileadmin/assets/Products/Drives_Documents/PD42-1240_CANopen_firmware_manual_Fw3.22_Rev1.01.pdf"], ["CANopen Firmware Manual FW V3.21 Rev V1.00", "https://trinamic.com/fileadmin/us